# SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0
# Trustfile — Trust boundaries and integrity invariants for 0patch-lsa-sentinel
# Author: Jonathan D.A. Jewell <j.d.a.jewell@open.ac.uk>
#
# Defines what LLM/SLM agents are trusted to do without asking, and integrity
# invariants that verify the repo has not been tampered with.

@abstract:
Trust boundaries and integrity checks for 0patch-lsa-sentinel. Defines what AI
agents may do autonomously and what requires human approval, plus checks that
verify repository integrity. Default posture is fail-safe-deny.
@end

## Trust Levels

The 0patch-lsa-sentinel operates at trust level: standard

Trust levels:
- maximal:    Agent may read, build, test, lint, format, heal freely.
- standard:   Agent may read, build, test, lint. Licence/audit edits and
              destructive/external actions require approval.
- restricted: Agent may read only. All modifications need approval.
- minimal:    Agent may read specific files only.

Current trust level: standard

## Deny Areas (require explicit human approval)

### licence-files
- description: LICENSE, LICENSES/, and SPDX headers must never be auto-edited
- areas:
  - LICENSE
  - LICENSES/
- severity: critical
- notes: Flag licence drift; do not fix it automatically.

### audit-docs
- description: Audit documents must never be deleted or rewritten by an agent
- areas:
  - AUDIT.adoc
  - AFFIRMATION.adoc
  - audits/
- severity: critical

### verified-kernel
- description: The SPARK classifier + Idris2 ABI carry proofs; changes need review
- areas:
  - core-spark/src/
  - abi-idris2/src/
- severity: warning

## Integrity Invariants

### no-secrets-committed
- description: No credential files in repo
- run: test ! -f .env && test ! -f credentials.json && test ! -f .env.local
- severity: critical

### no-private-keys
- description: No private key files committed
- run: "! find . -name '*.pem' -o -name 'id_rsa' -o -name 'id_ed25519' 2>/dev/null | grep -q ."
- severity: critical

## Provenance

### author-correct
- description: Git author matches expected identity
- run: "git log -1 --format='%ae' | grep -qE '(hyperpolymath|j\\.d\\.a\\.jewell)'"
- severity: warning

### license-content
- description: LICENSE is the canonical MPL-2.0 text
- run: grep -q 'Mozilla Public License Version 2.0' LICENSE
- severity: warning

## Fail-Safe

### deny-on-ambiguity
- description: When a permission or invariant is ambiguous, deny and escalate
- run: echo "fail-safe-deny is the default posture for this repository"
- severity: advisory
